en_text: The astronauts will once again be using Orion for their reentry,
jp_text: パラシュｰト事故の時と同じく➡

en_text: It comes down to whether the parachute you designed will properly deploy.
jp_text: 君が仕込んだパラシュートが➡

en_text: In the Comeback Competition, Pieco, our rover, placed fifth out of fifteen.
What should we do with Pieco?

jp_text: もう決まってるんじゃない？

en_text: I'll see you back on Earth,
jp_text: 地球で また会おう 日々人｡

en_text: It'll be lonely without you guys...
jp_text: さびしくなるぜ チクショー｡

en_text: Fuel, oxygen, power, launch speed confirmed.
All right, begin the final countdown.
jp_text: よし 最終カウントダウン開始！
ロシアチームのルーニエ２号｡➡

en_text: You hold onto Pieco for us.
jp_text: ピエコは あんたが預かってくれ｡
それが 俺の仕事だ》

en_text: Grow up to be a big boy.
jp_text: 大きい男になるんだぞ｡
google_translated: It will be a big man.

en_text: You can tell he's my son.
I didn't mean that Hibito would do the docking.
jp_text: あ いや…日々人はしね～けど…｡
google_translated: Oh ... Despite my daily person, but ....

jp_text: 私にも そ～いう時期はあった｡
google_translated: There was a time to say that.

en_text: He'll be even more popular than he already is...
and I don't know what to do for him when he returns.
jp_text: 何かしてやれることもない｡➡

en_text: We're supposed to be on vacation.
jp_text: せっかくの休みなのに～≫
google_translated: Even though it is a holiday ~ »

en_text: This is going to be a success.
They manage the astronauts' health as long as they're in space.

jp_text: でもねっ でもねっ 六太がね➡
google_translated: But even if it is huge

jp_text: オリオン こちらヒューストン｡➡

en_text: In thirty-five minutes, you'll be entering the atmosphere.

jp_text: 《ピコにとっても この帰還は…》

en_text: They will use the same method of entry as three years ago.
jp_text: ３年前の事故と同じ方法ですが…｡
google_translated: It is the same way as an accident for three years ....

jp_text: パラシュート 展開成功！
サーチ＆レスキュー 急行せよ！
ただ今 ヒューストンに到着です！
google_translated: I'm just arriving at Houston now!
